    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nWhen the sign column is set, scrolling through text with long lines causes the lines to occasionally wrap incorrectly, where the first character of the word that should be on the next line is still visible on the same line, and the next line appears in the sign column (and number column, if enabled).\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nSet the terminal to be reasonably narrow.\r\n```\r\nnvim --clean lorem.txt\r\n:set signcolumn=yes\r\n:set number        # optional, but if unset you must set signcolumn to yes:3 or similar\r\n:set smoothscroll  # optional but makes reproducing the bug easier\r\n```\r\nScroll up and down a couple of times.\r\n\r\nIf on Linux, I need to additionally set `linebreak` and `smoothscroll` is not optional.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nText does not bleed over semi-randomly into the sign column.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nv0.11.0-dev-414+g49ba36bec\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nNo, 9.1\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nmacOS 14.5\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\niTerm2 3.5.3 and Alacritty 0.13.2 (1)\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\n`xterm-256color` and `alacritty`\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nHomebrew",
