            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "1. Anything that causes enough line brakes. I can specifically reproduce this with a terminal width of 70 characters (`columns` is 70, `lines` is 46).\r\n2. Lorem Ipsum text (attached: [`lorem.txt`](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/16230929/lorem.txt)).\r\n3. Mouse wheel / trackpad.\r\n\r\nMinimal reproduction configuration on macOS with both the Homebrew build and the latest nightly build using above column and line lengths.\r\n```lua\r\nvim.opt.signcolumn = \"yes:3\"\r\nvim.opt.smoothscroll = true  -- Optional but improves reproducibility\r\n```\r\nDemonstration of bad wrapping (macOS, iTerm2): https://asciinema.org/a/J26B3ZRCI06vvYW0JAnqjzarh.\r\n\r\nI can also reproduce this on Linux (Arch) using Alacritty and Terminator by additionally setting `linebreak`, which _seems_ to be the same bug.",
